<br>
So anyway. I want to group now. Waiting until I get greater team heal which will be soon. I was in a regular group in EQ for 6 months, everyday for 8+ hrs so I know about grouping. But I will be a noobi here. What nano's should I have set up on my bar? Do I use team heals, or greater healing touch? What about taunting nano's? What will people expect of me? I never wanted to be a healer cause I know how pissed off people get when they die. Is there a lot of that? Is BS the best place to group 100+? I am there all the time soloing now? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucelestiness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestiness</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#660000>(2/2/02 11:52:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1631.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noobi needs advice</span><hr size=1> ok...team advice for an MA<br>
me: lvl 164 MA (just so u know that i know what im talking about). <br>
<br>
hot keys: brawl, dimach of course. bwt (i assume u use this) or whatever special attack you use. and your weapon special attacks if you have them. this should all be a given. <br>
<br>
I use both the single heal and the team heal. i tend to use team heal more because even though it heals a bit less..it recharges faster. our heals are slow so if i team heal sometimes the mob has allready switched to whom it was attacking and i can get both goin. if its a really hard mob i tend to chain team heal. <br>
<br>
as far as what skills: get VS (if u dont allready have it get it asap), lma later on too. evade buffs and AC buffs. those are the buffs you will be asked to give. sometimes velocity also. and dirty fighter for the enforcers. if you are teamed with an NT get crunch and hummidity extractor from them. u will be the secondary and sometimes the only healer so you need as much nano as possible. dont worry about taunting nanos..they are a waste. <br>
<br>
and BS is the best place for after lvl 100..but it will be hard to get a team cuz most of the peeps there are lvl 130+. but not all of them.  <p>If you are going to Hell, you may as well have fun doing it.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ujuried.showPublicProfile?language=EN>juried</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#660000>(2/3/02 6:52:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1631.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noobi needs advice</span><hr size=1> thank you Celestiness. You have always been more than generous in sharing your MA experiences and they are very helpful to people that are coming up through the ranks like me.<br>
<br>
When you are in a group do tank with the other tanks or stay back saving your nano for team member heals? <br>
<br>
Also another thing I 've done lately is use nano kits rather than first aid, as this is a good way to get in a few extra heals before nano runs out. Is raising first aid a good straetgy? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#660000>(2/3/02 10:58:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1631.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/cjoiner/priest.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noobi needs advice</span><hr size=1> We've argued over that some.<br>
<br>
A few folks here have expressed the opinion that First Aid is a waste of IP.<br>
<br>
Personally, I find it well worthwhile, but I'm only L72 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#660000>(2/3/02 11:01:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1631.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/cjoiner/priest.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noobi needs advice</span><hr size=1> And I violently disagree with Celly saying get the AC buffs.<br>
<br>
It's not worth pouring the IP into Matt Crea, when it's not used for anything else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucelestiness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestiness</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#660000>(2/3/02 1:41:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1631.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> AC, first aid etc</span><hr size=1> Yeah..some dont do AC buffs. some do. I did cuz i started from day one and didnt know jack lol. If they did an IP wipe I would scrap my mat creation and go for all evades probably. but gettin up to greater shen or titanium skin isnt that bad of an investment in IPs really. especially when you title cap. With partial diamond skin i can often get hit for min dmg in pvm which is nice. Just depends how you want to play your character. <br>
<br>
as far as firt aid goes...im still using ql 90 first aids. i think..the one that heals for 450ish. id at least get up to the one that takes 318 in first aid. its great for that last resort insta heal that can get u to a zone in pvp if u r gettin ganked or when u r down in health to where if u get hit one more time u will die in a mission cuz our heals take so long.<br>
<br>
and i both tank and heal in missions. we do too good of dmg output (over time which is good in pvm) with our crits, brawls and bwt to not heal. and i pretty much just cast team heal when someone needs it. and i cast it early trying to keep the team at full health (unlike alot of docs who wait till u r half or so which i hate).  I mean honestly...most of the high lvl MAs i team with can cast at least i think greater shen and most titanium. just somethin to strive for when u title cap which is the only times i have added IP to MC cept early on. <br>
<br>
i only did mat met to get muscle booster....but its not really needed but great of gettinon that primus/flowers as it stacks with essence and general. but its the first buff i lose if i run out of room for more important buffs. only ads a few points of dmg. (at lvl 100 though a few points helps) but when fightin vets+ a few points is jack lol. <br>
<br>
like i said in other posts..its just one template. if i could change a few things i would. but i personally wouldnt change my AC buffs probably. just some other things i added to and didnt need early on.  <p>If you are going to Hell, you may as well have fun doing it.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucelestiness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestiness</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#660000>(2/3/02 10:15:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1631.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> also...</span><hr size=1> also...10 points of AC takes care of 1 point of dmg. so a 500 AC buff kills 50 points of dmg. well ad that to 10 hits of 200 from a mob lets say...with the extra 500 AC...its 150. thats alot of HP saved in one fight.  <p>If you are going to Hell, you may as well have fun doing it.</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1631.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1631.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1631.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1631.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/im